7. During early libc initialization (`__libc_chcore_init`), `fd_dic[1]->fd_op` was bound to the `stdout_ops` structure. The `.write` method inside `stdout_ops` points exactly to `chcore_stdout_write`.
8. Consequently, `chcore_write` delegates execution to `chcore_stdout_write(1, buf, count)`, completing the journey from a standard API down to a port-specific implementation.

